                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-04T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 4, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 4—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1063. Legation’s 1060, September 3, 3 p.m. Following from Mukden: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 3, noon. Referring to my telegram of September 2, 5 p.m.,
                            Japanese consular authorities undertake to do their utmost to ensure
                                <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_TRM1">Talbot</persName>’s safety in
                            railway concession but assume no responsibility for his protection
                            outside that area. In their opinion the situation is the result of his
                            continued presence and can be satisfactorily liquidated by his
                            departure. I am informing <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_TRM1"
                                >Talbot</persName> to this effect.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
